description: winter drought and cold temperatures on the East side of the cascades causes the trees to blow up in high altitude due to the chemical additions in cells/cytoplasm that lower the freezing point, then the roots freeze, and the needles exposed to sun still try and photosynthesize, the stomata opens and gas exchange occurs, water in leaf is forced to evaporation and therefore conifers are better at this… larch looses its needles which is an adaptation to this and therefore don’t have to photosynthesize when the roots are frozen but needles are exposed to sun.
